d old, for hundreds of years. The intricate illustrations draw on centuries-old painting styles and on natural imagery and everyday life in Vietnam.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBui, Hoai Mai.1 aMai, Bui Hoai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNguyen, Nguyet Cam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSachs, Dana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082484048840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824840488423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780824840488/original  a978-3-11-056414-3  UHP eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066325-9  University of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK